The Kaduna Police Command has began the screening of over 9,000 new applicants who applied to be recruited into the Nigerian Police Force as constables This was disclosed on Sunday by the Command’s Public Relations Officer, ASP Mohammed Jalige According to him, the command has already screened over 2000 applicants from 15 Local Government areas of the state.
He mentioned the 15 Local Governments area to include;
Birnin Gawri, Chikun, Giwa, Igabi, Ikara, Jaba, Jama’a, Kachia, Kaduna North, Kaduna South, Kajuru, Kaura, Kauru, Kagarko and Kubau, while the remaining eight LGAs -Kudan, Lere, Makarfi, Sabon Gari, Sanga, Soba, Zangon Kataf and Zaria.
He said, the command would continued the screening of the remaining applicants on February 7, 2022. He urged the intending applicants, who have already applied to make themselves available for the screening. The command had earlier announced that the physical and credential screening of applicant police constables of the state’s origin would begin from February 1 to February 20 at the Police College, Kaduna. He appealed to all applicants to adhere to COVID -19 protocols.